    <h3 class="CaseHeading">Case Study - Cindi F.:  42 year old female, BMI = 39.8, otherwise healthy</h3>
    <div>
        <p class="CaseDetails">Cindi has no family history of health problems, is on no medications, and using no supplements.</p>
        <p class="CaseDetails">
            Cindi was first seen by Christine on July 11, 2012.&nbsp; She shared with Christine
            that she didn't like most food, currently was not really eating any vegetables,
            fruits, pasta, or seafood.&nbsp; She did not enjoy eating or figuring out what to
            eat.&nbsp; Even though she did not like many foods and was exercising regularly
            (including sessions with a trainer), she could not seem to lose weight.&nbsp; Her
            goals were to lose weight, find nutritious foods that she would be willing to eat,
            and to set a good example for her infant son.&nbsp; Cindi was very willing to try
            new foods, she just didn't know where to start or how to go about balancing her
            meals to ensure she was meeting her nutritional needs.&nbsp; Christine worked with
            her to identify new foods to try, how to try them, as well as the frequency with
            which to try them.&nbsp; Christine also explained the role of various nutrients
            in overall health as well as weight management to help Cindi develop a long-term
            plan to achieve her goals.&nbsp; By Cindi's third appointment, she had incorporated
            more than 9 different vegetables into her eating plan, as well as 4 different fruits
            that she really enjoyed.&nbsp; She also added some whole grains and seeds that she
            had never had before, had lost weight (BMI down to 37.2), and was well on her way
            of achieving her health and nutrition goals.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
