<h3>5-Step System for Transforming Your Health</h3>
<div>
    <p>Do you feel like you already eat healthy and exercise, but are not getting the results you want?</p>
    
    <div>(Click for more details)</div>
    <div class="accordion">
        <h3 class="CaseHeading">Case Study - Victor A.:  29 year old male diagnosed with hypothyroidism</h3>
        <div>
            <p class="CaseDetails">
                Victor's hypothyroidism was well controlled with medication.&nbsp; His family medical
                history includes cancer, high blood pressure, heart surgery, and thyroid conditions.&nbsp;
                His goals were to improve his own meal preparation skills, learn what kind of foods
                are most nutritious for him to keep his thyroid hormones under control, and to maintain
                a healthy weight.
            </p>
            <p class="CaseDetails">
                At his initial appointment with Christine on August 10, 2012, he weighed 208 pounds
                and had a BMI of 24.0.&nbsp; After analyzing his food log, Christine discovered
                that he was actually NOT eating enough calories to support his exercise routine.&nbsp;
                He was also eating too much protein, not enough carbohydrate and not enough fiber.&nbsp;
                Christine provided him with an example menu utilizing his food preferences while
                still meeting his needs.&nbsp; She also provided him with an instruction sheet of
                how to slowly increase his fiber and carbohydrates to allow his body to adjust without
                causing digestive problems.&nbsp; At his second appointment, he had lost a few pounds
                and his body fat had decreased 2 percentage points.&nbsp; By his final appointment,
                his body fat had decreased to 9%, even though his weight had gone up to 209 pounds.&nbsp;
                He also brought in results from his wellness check up (two days prior) that showed
                improvement in all areas (waist size, blood pressure, etc.).&nbsp; He was comfortable
                with his weight and he now knew what a healthy range was for his height.&nbsp; He
                became confident in knowing how to prepare healthy meals, as well as how to choose
                foods from his worksite cafeteria while maintaining his health and fitness goals.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

